  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>MAD Mount Hotel is offered on a half board basis with breakfast and dinner taken in the hotels onsite restaurant.</p>
<p>Breakfast consists of continental buffet served between 7am - 10am.</p>
<p>Dinner is served between 6:30pm - 9:30pm. The hotel <span>offers a variety of dishes inspired by Italian cuisine and other flavours from around the world - Pizzas, Japanese Tuna tataki, and swiss grilled cheese among others, are on the menu too, combined with local beers and wines. Vegetarian options are also available.</span></p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Located just steps away from the <span>Nendaz telecabine, this hotel is in a central location in Nendaz resort, giving you easy access to all the resort amenities and the 4 Valleys ski area. </span></p>
<h2>Restaurant and bar</h2>
<p>The hotel has it's own restaurant where you'll have your half board meals. You'll have the opportunity to try a variety of different foods. On the menu you'll find dishes inspired by Italian cuisine, Japanese cuisine and traditional Swiss delicacies. </p>
<p>The terrace bar allows you to appreciate the outdoors from the warmth of the inside. The large open windows give panoramic views of the surrounding mountains which are the perfect backdrop for an evening filled with local cocktails and wine.</p>
<h2>Luxury spa </h2>
<p>Despite it's small and cosy size, the MAD Mount offers you a range of spa facilities included during your stay. The hotels luxury spa area has 7 wellness amenities for you to use to unwind after an energetic day out on the mountain. Make the most of the hammam and tropical sauna, or relax not just your body but your mind too in the Japanese Onsen - a natural hot spring.</p>
<h2>Sustainability MAD</h2>
<p>MAD Mount Hotel takes pride in it's reputation as the first carbon neutral hotel in the whole of Switzerland. Throughout the hotel, you'll find various notes to the great outdoors. All of of the bedrooms are built in a cabin-inspired design, using locally sourced wood and natural materials - even the floors are made from 98% organic and recyclable materials! During your stay, you'll also benefit from the hotels natural insulation, so not only will you be getting warm and toasty in the comforts of a log cabin bedroom, you'll also feel great doing it. </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
